Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.42,0:00:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You found a job as a waitress\Nand a place to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.43,0:00:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But this bed is awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.22,0:00:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It almost falls over\Njust when I sit on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.89,0:00:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It will collapse if you lie on it, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.64,0:00:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll sleep on this bed.\NYou're better off sleeping on that sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no bed here for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.07,0:00:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.19,0:00:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You go back to Dr. Reichwein in Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.28,0:00:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.66,0:00:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?\NYou need to go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.74,0:00:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.74,0:00:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how will you learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.75,0:00:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll teach me, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.83,0:00:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,School is not the only thing.\NYou'll never make friends like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.09,0:00:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got friends. You and Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.51,0:00:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, you know\Nyou'll be lonely without me around, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.22,0:00:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice try, but you're going back to Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.02,0:00:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! I'm not going to Munich!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.23,0:01:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Nina.\NAre you going there again today?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.99,0:01:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Give it up, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.41,0:01:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day, you go to the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.66,0:01:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times you go,\Nyou'll never remember anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.42,0:01:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.38,0:02:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where we lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.63,0:02:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother and I… and Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.61,0:03:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, Johan was\Ndragged down these stairs and taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.83,0:03:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Don't! Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.87,0:03:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother! Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.42,0:03:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.46,0:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina is the name I use now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.09,0:03:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But what name did I have then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.10,0:03:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina? Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.27,0:03:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What is…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.15,0:03:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.82,0:03:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The car Johan was taken in\Nwent down this road.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping secrets from him is a no-no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.33,0:04:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Children gathered\Nfor what were called book readings…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.21,0:04:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,here at the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.84,0:04:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The lock's been broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, they tried to create\Nsuperior students.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.11,0:04:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a superior student?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.12,0:04:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.99,0:04:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.21,0:04:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:04:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.26,0:05:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan ran away…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.68,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,through the rose bushes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.43,0:05:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.32,0:05:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.48,0:05:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This pain…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.94,0:05:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This pain…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.32,0:05:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.28,0:05:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,THREE FROGS.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.04,0:05:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I waited in this room…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.37,0:05:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for Mother to return…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.83,0:05:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and for Johan to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.29,0:05:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I read this picture book as I waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.26,0:05:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,THE NAMELESS MONSTER
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.26,0:05:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,People can become…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever they want to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.43,0:05:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonaparta, the man who held\Nthe book readings at the Red Rose Mansion…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.60,0:05:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I read his book here in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.52,0:05:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was waiting for Johan to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.69,0:06:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I smiled and faced the door…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.61,0:06:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and said…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.53,0:06:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.12,0:06:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"Welcome back."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.83,0:06:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.75,0:06:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.21,0:06:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.38,0:06:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.72,0:06:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.64,0:06:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.14,0:06:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.43,0:06:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The door never opened!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.23,0:06:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when I said "Welcome back,"\Nthe door didn't open!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.32,0:06:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't open! It won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.53,0:06:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember now! I…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.65,0:06:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.62,0:06:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to remember!\NYou don't have to remember anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.16,0:06:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same with me!\NI've got tons of awful memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.66,0:06:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't have\Nto remember them anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.04,0:06:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! I'll go to Dr. Reichwein!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.59,0:07:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll come with me!\NWe'll go back together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.80,0:07:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do what Tenma said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.39,0:07:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, let's make…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.56,0:07:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,happy memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.15,0:07:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,PRAGUE POLICE STATION\N(CZECH REPUBLIC)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.16,0:07:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a minute, Chief Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.41,0:07:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How come I can only\Nsit next to the detective and listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.62,0:07:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We're doing our very best\Nto accommodate your request.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.38,0:07:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Your very best?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.21,0:07:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only giving me\N30 minutes with each person!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.21,0:07:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can listen in. Isn't that enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.80,0:07:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to realize that even allowing\Nthis is an extreme exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.35,0:07:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It took a lot for us to even\Nbe able to question five witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.89,0:08:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But we should take this chance\Nto get as much info as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.52,0:08:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-You just don't get it.\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.73,0:08:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These people were kids\Nin that book reading club.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.36,0:08:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't want to talk about their pasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.74,0:08:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I doubt there's any question\Nthat all the bones that were found
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,are somehow connected with\Nthe former Czechoslovakia secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.63,0:08:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth around these kinds of things\Nusually remains a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.80,0:08:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the detective\Nin charge of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.81,0:08:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the attorney,\NMr. Verdemann, from Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.94,0:08:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Detective Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.98,0:08:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.69,0:08:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already made a list of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.28,0:08:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Please only do as I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.78,0:08:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only here as an observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.62,0:09:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,3 Cerveny Street,\Notherwise known as the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.92,0:09:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how it looks now\Nthat it's burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.42,0:09:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true that you participated
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.59,0:09:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book readings\Nthat took place here in 1968, Mr. Erno?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.72,0:09:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.18,0:09:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know a man\Nby the name of Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.65,0:09:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you please keep quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.61,0:09:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.19,0:09:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do this carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.23,0:09:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get nothing out of them\Nby being careful. Do you want that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.16,0:09:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no idea how much trouble\Nwe went through to get this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.41,0:09:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.20,0:09:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought this mansion\Nwas my emotional foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.37,0:09:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But seeing the mansion burn down,\NI thought… How do I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.92,0:09:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd feel sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.51,0:09:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you feel nostalgic for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.93,0:09:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nostalgia?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.43,0:09:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. This place was\Nlike a school to you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.10,0:10:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann! Please keep quiet!\NOnly the questions I prepared--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.98,0:10:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I do…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.11,0:10:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadness… Nostalgia…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.15,0:10:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't know…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.74,0:10:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotional scars? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.82,0:10:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, did your participation\Nin the book readings
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.37,0:10:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,have any effect on your life now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.83,0:10:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.88,0:10:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How about on your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.17,0:10:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to answer that.\NThat's your right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.34,0:10:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't like my wife\Nand I were on bad terms or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.01,0:10:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Our children…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.06,0:10:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of our sons killed themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.61,0:10:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't have\Nany problems in particular,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.23,0:10:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but for some reason, they both…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.61,0:10:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why they killed themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.45,0:10:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.66,0:11:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that your questions\Nare too much by the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.83,0:11:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How much information have you\Ngotten using them anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.42,0:11:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're typical of youngsters nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you go by the book\Nwhen you pick up women too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you, my father?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.85,0:11:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a father,\Nbut I sure wouldn't want one like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.65,0:11:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.90,0:11:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of the book readings, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.61,0:11:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us anything you remember,\Nno matter how trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.70,0:11:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"The God of Peace is always very busy."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.86,0:11:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.87,0:11:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"He was so busy playing the horn,\Nhe had no time to look in the mirror."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's from The God of Peace\Nby Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.50,0:11:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know this, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I kind of remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I also liked the one
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.80,0:11:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that was about a monster who went west\Nand a monster who went east.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.34,0:12:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you like about these books?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.55,0:12:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well… How can I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like they took me away\Nto a different world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A different world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.73,0:12:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and let's see…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.36,0:12:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like things like sadness,\Njoy and fear didn't exist there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.74,0:12:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did those books\Nmake you feel that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.95,0:12:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I basically wouldn't feel anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.83,0:12:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't even need my name anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.79,0:12:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was real freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.33,0:12:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.25,0:12:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did it feel that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.21,0:12:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta taught you there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.13,0:12:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that was the name\Nof the guy who read to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.30,0:12:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These are your clearest memories\Nof what happened at the book readings?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.60,0:12:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My clearest memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.23,0:12:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.60,0:12:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, a man came to that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.90,0:12:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he was from a radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.94,0:13:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he liked the song\N"Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.74,0:13:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and told us the story of The Wizard of Oz.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.95,0:13:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that man like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.38,0:13:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,-Pull yourself together!\N-Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.00,0:13:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Please! Tell me anything you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.26,0:13:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like\Nthis questioning is personal to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.39,0:13:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's personal for you too, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.85,0:13:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The young detective who had those murders
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.35,0:13:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,connected to\Nthe secret police pinned on him…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.23,0:13:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was you, right, Detective Suk?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.98,0:13:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're desperate\Nto clear yourself of suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.53,0:13:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.82,0:13:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.32,0:13:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was imprisoned\Nas a spy for former East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.91,0:13:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I always believed he was falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.66,0:13:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But my father really was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.09,0:13:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.80,0:14:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe anything\Nin this world anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.05,0:14:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, by pursuing the case\Nof another falsely accused man,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.14,0:14:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I am trying to find\Nsomething to believe in again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.68,0:14:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The man from a radio station\Nthis man talked about…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.23,0:14:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He's my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.19,0:14:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My father might have been involved\Nin the brainwashing experiments
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.15,0:14:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that occurred at the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.86,0:14:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We must not look away\Nif we want to learn the real truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.08,0:14:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, can I leave now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.71,0:14:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.71,0:14:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy I told you about earlier,\Nhe told me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.17,0:14:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"Get out of here fast."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.13,0:14:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,"You'll find a beautiful place\Nover the rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.51,0:14:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's where your family is."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.68,0:14:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"At the end of The Wizard of Oz,\NDorothy makes it back home."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.64,0:14:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"So you get out of here fast too."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.69,0:15:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I left that mansion forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.53,0:15:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.45,0:15:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and kids are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.24,0:15:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.09,0:15:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We must not look away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.59,0:15:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.26,0:15:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two people left to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Let's continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.98,0:15:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, don't stare off into space!\NHold onto this properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.69,0:15:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your desk, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.90,0:15:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.53,0:15:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina doesn't want to talk about\Nwhat happened to her in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,From what you told me, it sounds like\Nshe got a lot of her memories back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.17,0:16:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems she was stopped\Nfrom remembering until the very end…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.67,0:16:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.47,0:16:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it wrong for me to stop her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.22,0:16:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No. You did very well, Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.81,0:16:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's finish this up quick\Nso I can have some weisswurst and beer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.40,0:16:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We ate all the weisswurst last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.61,0:16:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! What will I do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.53,0:16:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.15,0:16:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought you some of your favorite,\Nweisswurst sausages.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.49,0:16:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys sure are considerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein, how have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.96,0:16:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry\Nthat I haven't written in so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.17,0:16:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I've made you worry, but I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.22,0:16:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,, Dr. Reichwein, I have a favor to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.55,0:16:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the woman Eva Heinemann,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.81,0:16:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain organization is after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.43,0:17:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent her to you.\NPlease take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.65,0:17:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take care of Nina\Nand Dieter as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.69,0:17:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be long now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.40,0:17:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe this is the only way\Nfor me to end all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.16,0:17:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"From Kenzo Tenma."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.92,0:17:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That letter arrived three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But Eva hasn't reached out to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.38,0:17:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Where was this letter sent from?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.88,0:17:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to read the postmark.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.39,0:17:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you figure it out, Karl?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.81,0:17:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I think I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll know where Tenma is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.27,0:17:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm bothered by this last sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.77,0:17:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"I believe this is the only way\Nfor me to end all this."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.37,0:17:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then.\NLet's finish up this desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.54,0:18:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My hand might not be so steady\Nafter that drink though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.34,0:18:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.96,0:18:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to remember everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.38,0:18:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you prepared for what you'll find?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.35,0:18:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.56,0:18:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm ready to use whatever method\Nit takes to remember everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.81,0:18:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest, I'd rather not do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.98,0:18:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But if that's truly what you want,\Nthen okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.95,0:18:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about this, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.57,0:18:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Dr. Gillen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.70,0:18:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-But…\N-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.54,0:18:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm about to reveal under hypnosis\Njust might be terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.75,0:18:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think you can handle it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.34,0:18:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll be fine.\NWe'll face these things together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.18,0:18:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now. Close your eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.80,0:18:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,take a deep breath,\Nand relax your whole body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.81,0:19:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your mother like?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.36,0:19:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.82,0:19:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother… was kind…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.53,0:19:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She sang…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.45,0:19:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She sang in… a beautiful voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.87,0:19:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell of bean soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.58,0:19:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.79,0:19:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Father…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.75,0:19:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Father was… a government soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.76,0:19:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A government soldier?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.55,0:19:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you met him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.93,0:19:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.51,0:19:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother told me…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.39,0:19:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Father was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.69,0:19:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother was a political activist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.23,0:19:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When your father was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.03,0:19:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your mother, who was\Na political activist, then defected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.24,0:19:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Was she running from someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.62,0:20:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,At the Three Frogs… we hid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.75,0:20:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But my brother…\Nwas captured by the man with glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.50,0:20:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brother was captured, was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.30,0:20:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.26,0:20:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So many people… dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.34,0:20:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brother saw that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.01,0:20:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow! Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.97,0:20:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow! The rose thorns hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.69,0:20:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.94,0:20:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.61,0:20:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.95,0:20:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured out\Nwhere Tenma's letter was sent from.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.53,0:20:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.74,0:20:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.49,0:20:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, you've remembered everything,\Nhaven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.21,0:20:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I… am not Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.71,0:20:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.71,0:20:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.17,0:20:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.\NDon't be afraid. You can tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.47,0:20:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.97,0:21:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.64,0:21:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. Don't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.06,0:21:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.52,0:21:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.23,0:21:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.11,0:21:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll… clap my hands now. When I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.24,0:21:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.62,0:21:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.71,0:21:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.50,0:21:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I… just say something terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.59,0:21:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No. When you were under hypnosis,\Nyou refused to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.64,0:21:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have remembered everything now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.81,0:21:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,TWO DAYS LATER
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.48,0:22:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein and Dieter,\Nplease forgive me for leaving so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.24,0:22:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to Frankfurt, where Tenma is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.54,0:22:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know everything now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.21,0:22:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.37,0:22:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where Johan came from\Nand where he's trying to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.88,0:22:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go, then all this\Ncan be brought to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.42,0:22:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go, then Tenma can be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.77,0:23:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitle translation by: Brian Athey
